{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"193c5311-c749-4ab","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key findings:\n\n1. `--accent-weak: #2a2347` exists in main.scss and is USED in 3 P10 files (tailwind.config.ts, login.vue, FormField.vue). The plan's tokens.scss lists legacy aliases but does NOT include `--accent-weak`. This is a missing-token issue that will break P10 pages. High severity — the plan explicitly claims \"Legacy app-utility tokens kept so P10 pages don't break\" but omits --accent-weak which is actively used.\n\n2. Canonical tokens from rules: `--bg #0D0F17, --surface #181B25, --surface-2 #222635, --stroke #30364A, --text #F4F0E8, --muted #9EA7B8, --magic #B9A7FF (FIXED brand), --mana #8FD7C7, --xp #F6C76B, --blue #7EA7FF, --danger #FF6B7A`. Current main.scss has --bg #0e0f12, --surface #171a20, --surface-2 #1f232b, --text #e7e9ee, --muted #9aa0ab, --accent #7c5cff (lilac!). The plan says tokens.scss will have ALL canonical color tokens. Good. But plan also says \"Replace existing :root block with @use './tokens.scss'\". OK.\n\n3. The plan mentions `--accent default = #7dd3fc` (from catalog, non-lilac). Good. Currently --accent is #7c5cff (lilac) — must change.\n\n4. tokens.scss LOC ~110. The plan lists a LOT of tokens (canonical colors + semantic aliases + legacy + non-color + background/card/profile tints). 110 LOC might be tight but plausible. Not a hard issue.\n\n5. The plan says `apps/mobile/visual.ts (~3 LOC) — export * from '../shared/visual'`. But the ALLOWED WRITE PATHS list `shared/visual/**` and `apps/mobile/app/assets/**` and specific component files. `apps/mobile/visual.ts` is NOT in the allowed write paths. Wait — allowed paths: \"shared/visual/**, apps/mobile/app/assets/**, apps/mobile/app/components/Logo.vue, apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue, apps/mobile/app/assets/css/tokens.scss, and MAY touch apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts / apps/mobile/app/app.vue / apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main