s not a P10 auth page — it's a UI component. And login.vue IS a P10 auth page.\n\nActually, the PROJECT_RULES explicitly enumerate the P10 legacy vars and `--accent-weak` is not among them. So maybe the intent is that `--accent-weak` is NOT a P10 legacy var and the plan is correct to drop it? But then login.vue would break... unless login.vue is expected to be updated. But the rules say \"Must NOT touch P10 auth pages.\" This is a genuine conflict. The plan should preserve `--accent-weak` to avoid breaking login.vue. I'll raise this as high.\n\nLet me also verify the `--accent-grad` definition. Plan says `--accent-grad (linear-gradient(var(--magic), var(--blue)))`. But the old value was `linear-gradient(135deg, #7c5cff 0%, #4dd4ff 100%)` using accent colors. The new one uses --magic (#B9A7FF, FIXED brand lilac) and --blue (#7EA7FF). This changes the visual appearance of `.text-grad` and login button. But since tokens are being rebranded, this is expected. Not an issue.\n\nWait — PROJECT_RULES say --magic is \"FIXED brand\" and #B9A7FF is lilac-ish. And \"NO lilac\" in accent catalog. But --magic is a fixed brand color, not an accent. So using --magic in --accent-grad is OK per rules. Fine.\n\nLet me also check: does the plan's tokens.scss define `--accent` as runtime default `#7dd3fc`? Yes. But `--accent` should be RUNTIME from VisualState.accent_color. The tokens.scss provides a fallback default. That's fine — the mapper will override it at runtime. OK.\n\n5. Let me check the scatter self-check pattern. Plan says `if (process.argv[1] === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))`. This requires importing `fileURLToPath` from `node:url` and `import.meta.url`. In a `.ts` file run via `npx tsx`, this should work. Fine.\n\n6. visual-state.ts imports `from '../contracts/visual-settings'` — shared/visual/visual-state.ts → `../contracts/visual-settings` = shared/contracts/visual-settings. Correct path.\n\n7. The plan says `apps/mobile/visual.ts` is ~3 LOC `export * from '../shared/visual'`. As noted, path is wrong. Should be `../../shared/visual`.\n\nLet me finalize. I have 4 solid issues. Let me also consider whether the `nuxt.config.ts` head theme-color `#0e0f12` (old value) needs updating to new `--bg` #0D0F17. The plan says \"MAY touch nuxt.config.ts ONLY to wire tokens + background.\" The theme-color meta is still `#0e0f12` (old). Not critical — it's a meta tag color. Skip as nit.\n\nActually, one more: the plan says VisualBackground.vue reads `decorativeDetail` prop with default 'soft-sparks', but app.vue wiring (#11) doesn't mention passing any prop to VisualBackground. So it'll always use the default. For P09-1 that's acceptable (wiring comes later). Not an issue.\n\nLet me also check: does `bun run typecheck` exist?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_94d2a6912b9f4247b126340e","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /usr/projects/Диплом && cat apps/mobile/package.json 2>/dev/null | grep -A2 typecheck; echo \"---\"; rg \"accent-weak\" apps/mobile/app/pages/login.vue -n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"polza","model":"z-ai/glm-5.2","usage":{"input":1656,"output":2256,"cacheRead":8320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782864966989,"responseId":"gen_2183390942902489089"},"timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:17:05.824Z","cwd":"/usr/projects/Диплом"}
