IS used by P10 login.vue and FormField.vue. This breaks P10. High. Also tailwind.config references accent-weak color but that's tailwind utility not CSS var necessarily. The login.vue uses var(--accent-weak). So missing --accent-weak breaks login. High.\n\n9. scatter.ts self-check uses `process.argv[1] === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)`. Needs `import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url'`. Fine, runnable via npx tsx. OK.\n\n10. visual-state.ts uses `import.meta.url`? It says use process.argv pattern. Fine.\n\n11. The plan's FALLBACK_VISUAL_STATE uses decorative_detail 'soft-sparks' — valid enum. background_variant 'midnight' valid. card_variant 'graphite' valid. profile_background 'calm-shapes' valid. Good.\n\n12. ACCENT_CATALOG matches PROJECT_RULES. Good. No lilac. Good.\n\n13. Logo.vue uses PNG as CSS mask. But brand assets: \"chubzik-logo.png (from logo.png)\". Where's logo.png? find returned nothing for logo.png. So source doesn't exist? Let me check. The find for logo.png returned nothing. So there's no logo.png to copy from. The plan says \"copy from logo.png\" but it doesn't exist. Hmm, maybe it's elsewhere. Let me verify.\n\nActually the find returned nothing. Let me double check — maybe assets exist elsewhere. This could be a high issue: source asset doesn't exist. But maybe the plan author knows of a logo elsewhere. Let me check more.\n\nLet me run a broader find.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0d3492c78a064ddf8ba07182","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /usr/projects/Диплом && find . -iname 'logo*' -not -path './.git/*' -not -path './node_modules/*' 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"---svg---\"; find . -iname '*.svg' -not -path './.git/*' -not -path './node_modules/*' -not -path './android/*' 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"---brand dirs---\"; find . -type d -iname 'brand' -not -path './.git/*' 2>/dev/null | head"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3f28ac2e70ae41c78d8f9063","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /usr/projects/Дипл