hubzik-logo.png (from logo.png)\" and \"SVGs already aria-hidden + currentColor. Verified.\" But there's no logo.png and no magic-*.svg files anywhere in the repo. The plan claims they're verified but they don't exist. This is an unverified-claim / file-not-exist issue. The 7 brand assets must be COPIED — but source assets don't exist. The plan says \"Verified\" falsely. HIGH (file-not-exist).\n\n4. **`apps/mobile/visual.ts` import path**: `export * from '../shared/visual'` — mirrors api.ts which does `export * from \"../../shared/api\"`. Wait, api.ts is at apps/mobile/api.ts and references `../../shared/api`? That's odd — apps/mobile/ → ../ = apps/, ../../ = root, then shared/api. Yes correct: apps/mobile/api.ts → ../../shared/api. But the plan says `apps/mobile/visual.ts` does `export * from '../shared/visual'` — that would be apps/shared/visual which is wrong. Should be `../../shared/visual` to mirror api.ts. This is a path bug. HIGH (wrong-path). Actually wait, let me re-read: \"apps/mobile/visual.ts (~3 LOC) — `export * from '../shared/visual'` (mirrors apps/mobile/api.ts pattern)\". api.ts uses `../../shared/api`. The plan wrote `../shared/visual` which is wrong. HIGH.\n\n5. **tokens.scss LOC ~110 but contains a LOT**: canonical tokens + semantic aliases + legacy utilities + non-color hierarchy + background/card/profile variant tints + safe-area. The plan says ~110 LOC. With all those token groups plus comments, 110 is plausible but the file also must include `--accent-weak` (missing). Project rule: files ≤150 LOC. 110 is fine. Not an issue.\n\n6. **`--bg` canonical is #0D0F17 but existing main.scss uses #0e0f12 and tailwind uses #0e0f12**: The plan introduces canonical tokens that CHANGE the existing --bg/--surface/--text/--muted values. P10 pages use these vars. Changing --bg from #0e0f12 to #0D0F17, --surface #171a20→#181B25, --text #e7e9ee→#F4F0E8, --muted #9aa0ab→#9EA7B8, --accent #7c5cff(lilac)→#7dd3fc. This is a visual shift for all P10 pages. PROJECT_RULES say \"Existing committed P09/P10 must NOT be reverted\" and P10 pages use legacy CSS vars. Changing the VALUES of --bg/--surface/--text/--muted/--accent is a regression risk for P10 visual. But the task IS to add visual foundation with canonical tokens. The canonical tokens are specified by the rules (visual-foundation.md §4). So this is intended. However, --accent default changing from lilac #7c5cff to #7dd3fc is the whole point. This is acceptable per rules. Not flagging.\n\nBut wait — the legacy `--accent` in main.scss is #7c5cff (lilac). The plan sets runtime --accent default = #7dd3fc. P10 pages using --accent will shift from lilac to sky-blue. Per rules, --accent is RUNTIME from VisualState.accent_color; backend catalog has no lilac. So lilac must go. OK intended.\n\n7. **`--accent-grad` definition**: Plan says `--accent-grad (linear-gradient(var(--magic), var(--blue)))`. But existing is `linear-gradient(135deg, #7c5cff 0%, #4dd4ff 100%)` — accent→accent-2. The plan redefines it as magic→blue. P10 AppButton.vue uses --accent-grad. This changes the gradient. Is this a contradiction with \"legacy app-utility tokens kept so P10 pages don't break\"? The token is kept but its VALUE changes. The rule says P10 mobile pages use legacy CSS vars — meaning the vars must EXIST, not necessarily identical values. Acceptable as part of foundation. But it's a subtle risk. I'll consider it a nit/acceptable since the whole point is retheming. Actually the rule \"Existing committed P09/P10 must NOT be reverted\" — redefining accent-grad from accent→accent-2 to magic→blue is arguably a visual revert of P10's intended look. Hmm. But the canonical tokens mandate --magic as FIXED brand and --accent runtime. This is genuinely ambiguous. I'll not raise it as the canonical token spec governs.\n\n8. **scatter.ts LAYOUT_TABLE asset names \"from registry\"**: assets.ts exports MAGIC_SVG_ASSETS list of 6 names. scatter.ts uses asset names from registry. OK consistent. But the SVGs don't exist yet (issue 3).\n\n9. **`npx tsx` for self-check**: shared/visual/scatter.ts and visual-state.ts use `if (process.argv[1] === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))`. This requires `import.meta.url` and `fileURLToPath` from 'node:url'. tsx supports this. OK. Acceptance gate says mapper self-check runnable via `npx tsx`. Good.\n\n10. **visual-state.ts imports from '../contracts/visual-settings'**: shared/visual/visual-state.ts → ../contracts/visual-settings = shared/contracts/visual-settings. Correct path. Good.\n\n11. **`apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main.scss` edit — Replace `:root{}` with `@use './tokens.scss'`**: With Sass `@use`, the tokens in tokens.scss `:root` would still emit since they're not namespaced-only. Actually `@use` includes the CSS rules from the used file. But `@use` must be at top of file before other rules. main.scss currently has `:root` then `*`, body, etc. Replacing :root block with `@use './tokens.scss';` at top — fine. But the plan also says \"Remove raw hex from main.scss\". The existing main.scss :root has raw hex — moving to tokens.scss. Good. But `@use` vs `@import`: plan says \"@use './tokens.scss'; (or @import)\". With `@use`, the `:root` in tokens.scss emits globally. OK.\n\n12. **Logo.vue uses PNG as CSS mask with `-webkit-mask url(brand/chubzik-logo.png)`**: The path `brand/chubzik-logo.png` — in Nuxt, `~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png` resolves via Vite. Using bare `url(brand/chubzik-logo.png)` in CSS won't resolve; needs `~` or `@` alias or absolute. The plan says \"~/assets/brand/\" pattern elsewhere. In Logo.vue `<style>` v-bind, the mask url should be `url('~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png')` or use a dynamic import. Bare `brand/chubzik-logo.png` is wrong. MEDIUM — but this is implementation detail; for plan, flag as unverified-claim that mask path will resolve. Actually the plan explicitly writes `-webkit-mask url(brand/chubzik-logo.png)`. That path is incorrect for Nuxt asset resolution. MEDIUM.\n\nActually, more importantly — using a PNG as a CSS mask is unreliable across browsers (mask with PNG alpha works in -webkit but PNG masks have poor support / color-mask won't tint a PNG the way SVG currentColor does). The plan says \"color via currentColor → token color\" for SVGs but Logo uses PNG mask with `background: var(--logo-color)`. A PNG mask CAN be tinted via mask + background-color. This works in modern webkit. But Capacitor Android WebView supports -webkit-mask. OK probably fine. I'll note path issue only.\n\n13. **VisualBackground.vue reads `decorativeDetail` prop default 'soft-sparks'**: But VisualState['decorative_detail'] union is \"soft-sparks\"|\"thin-rings\"|\"small-dots\". FALLBACK uses 'soft-sparks'. OK.\n\n14. **Acceptance: `cd apps/mobile && bun run typecheck`**: nuxt typecheck runs vue-tsc. The new components Logo.vue/VisualBackground.vue import from `~~/visual` or `../../visual`. Need types. visual.ts re-exports. Should be OK if paths resolve. nuxt alias `~~` = rootDir = apps/mobile. So `~~/visual` = apps/mobile/visual.ts. Good. But the plan didn't explicitly state the import alias in components. Minor.\n\n15. **tokens.scss includes background/card/profile variant tints as \"raw hex tints, only here\"**: PROJECT_RULES say \"Raw hex ONLY in tokens.scss + fallback theme file.\" So raw hex variant tints in tokens.scss OK. But the canonical token list in §4 doesn't include these variant tints — they're new. Are they allowed? The plan adds --bg-dark-ember etc. These are needed for background_variant mapping. visual-state.ts mapper outputs --bg-variant etc. but the actual tint hex lives in tokens.scss. OK consistent with rules.\n\nWait — visual-state.ts mapper returns `--bg-variant` etc as keys. But where do the hex values for dark-ember/deep-forest live? The plan says tokens.scss has --bg-dark-ember/--bg-deep-forest/--bg-midnight. So mapper outputs `--bg-variant: var(--bg-midnight)` (a var reference, not raw hex). Good — no raw hex in mapper except catalog/fallback. Consistent.\n\n16. **FALLBACK_VISUAL_STATE background_variant 'midnight'** — but VisualState union is \"dark-ember\"|\"deep-forest\"|\"midnight\". OK valid.\n\n17. The plan does NOT mention updating tailwind.config.ts which has raw hex (bg, surface, accent #7c5cff lilac, accent-weak, error, ok). tailwind.config.ts is NOT in allowed write paths. But it contains lilac #7c5cff raw hex and `accent-weak`. The acceptance gate \"rg raw hex only in tokens/fallback/asset-meta\" — tailwind.config.ts raw hex would fail this gate. But it's a committed P10 file outside allowed paths. This is a real acceptance-criteria conflict. The plan should acknowledge tailwind.config.ts is out of scope and the rg gate must be scoped to exclude it, OR the gate will fail. MEDIUM — acceptance-miss: the stated raw-hex rg gate will fail due to tailwind.config.ts and AppButton.vue rgba. The plan doesn't scope the rg command.\n\nLet me also check: does the acceptance gate \"rg Math.random (none in apps/shared visual)\" — scoped to shared visual. Good. \"rg fonts.googleapis|gstatic (none)\" — global, fine. \"rg raw hex only in tokens/fallback/asset-meta\" — this is the problem one. The plan's acceptance says \"raw hex only in tokens.scss + visual-state.ts (catalog/fallback) + assets (svg paths)\". This ignores tailwind.config.ts (#7c5cff etc) and AppButton.vue rgba(124,92,255). These will cause the gate to fail. The plan needs to scope the rg to allowed paths or acknowledge.\n\nLet me finalize the top issues:\n\n1. [high]file-not-exist @## Files to create §2 → source brand assets (logo.png, magic-*.svg) don't exist in repo; \"Verified\" claim is false — locate or create the 7 source assets before copying\n\n2. [high]wrong-path @## Files to create §7 → apps/mobile/visual.ts must use `../../shared/visual` not `../shared/visual` to mirror api.ts\n\n3. [high]p10-regression @## Files to create §1 → add `--accent-weak` token (used by login.vue, FormField.vue, tailwind); omitting it breaks P10 pages\n\n4. [medium]accept-miss @## Acceptance plan → scope the raw-hex rg to allowed paths; tailwind.config.ts and AppButton.vue contain committed raw hex outside write scope that will fail a global rg\n\n5. [medium]unverified-claim @## Files to create §8 → bare `url(brand/chubzik-logo.png)` won't resolve in Nuxt CSS; use `~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png` alias\n\nLet me double check #2 — api.ts content: `export * from \"../../shared/api\";`. Yes. Plan says visual.ts `export * from '../shared/visual'`. Wrong. Confirmed HIGH.\n\nLet me verify --accent-weak usage is real and would break. login.vue:83 `background: var(--accent-weak)`, FormField.vue:54. If tokens.scss omits --accent-weak, these resolve to nothing (transparent/invalid). Breaks P10. The plan's legacy token list explicitly enumerates which are kept and omits --accent-weak. HIGH confirmed.\n\nThat's 5 solid issues. Let me make sure none are nits. All real. Good.\n\nActually #4 — is tailwind.config.ts in allowed write paths? ALLOWED: shared/visual/**, apps/mobile/app/assets/**, Logo.vue, VisualBackground.vue, tokens.scss, MAY touch nuxt.config.ts/app.vue/main.scss. tailwind.config.ts NOT allowed. AppButton.vue NOT allowed. So the raw-hex acceptance gate as written (\"raw hex only in tokens.scss + visual-state.ts + assets\") is impossible. The plan must scope rg to the new/visual files. MEDIUM accept-miss. Good.\n\nLet me also reconsider whether changing --bg value is a P10 revert. The canonical §4 mandates --bg #0D0F17. Existing is #0e0f12. This is the foundation change — intended. Not flagging.\n\nOne more: the plan says tokens.scss ~110 LOC but lists a huge number of tokens. Could exceed 150? Canonical ~13 + aliases ~? + legacy ~8 + non-color ~15 + 3 bg + 3 card + 3 profile + comments. ~110 plausible. Not flagging LOC.\n\nFinal answer with 5 issues.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"{\"ok\":false,\"feedback\":\"[high]file-not-exist @## Files to create §2 → source brand assets (logo.png, magic-*.svg, tiny-spark.svg) do not exist anywhere in the repo; \\\"Verified\\\" claim is false — locate/create the 7 source assets before copying\\n[high]wrong-path @## Files to create §7 → apps/mobile/visual.ts must re-export from `../../shared/visual`, not `../shared/visual`, to mirror the existing apps/mobile/api.ts path\\n[high]p10-regression @## Files to create §1 → add `--accent-weak` token (used by login.vue:83, FormField.vue:54, tailwind.config.ts); omitting it breaks committed P10 pages\\n[medium]accept-miss @## Acceptance plan → scope the raw-hex rg to allowed paths; tailwind.config.ts (#7c5cff lilac) and AppButton.vue rgba(124,92,255) are committed raw-hex outside write scope and will fail a global rg gate\\n[medium]unverified-claim @## Files to create §8 → bare `url(brand/chubzik-logo.png)` will not resolve in Nuxt/Vite CSS; use the `~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png` alias\",\"phase\":\"plan\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"polza","model":"z-ai/glm-5.2","usage":{"input":10476,"output":3776,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782865136262,"responseId":"gen_2183391652935241729"},"timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:20:32.646Z","cwd":"/usr/projects/Диплом"}
